# Habit Tracker

## Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Supabase for auth and database
- Recharts for charts
- Claude API via Anthropic SDK for AI insights
- Deployed on Vercel

## Database
- `habits` table: id (uuid), user_id (uuid, references auth.users), name (text), frequency (text), category (text), archived (boolean), created_at (timestamptz)
- `context_logs` table: id (uuid), user_id (uuid, references auth.users), habit_id (uuid, references habits), date (date), completed (boolean), sleep_score (integer 1-5), stress_score (integer 1-5), mood (text), schedule_disrupted (boolean), notes (text), created_at (timestamptz)
- RLS enabled on both tables, all policies use `auth.uid() = user_id`
- Migrations live in supabase/migrations/, run with `npx supabase db push`

## Architecture
- Supabase browser client: lib/supabase/client.ts
- Supabase server client: lib/supabase/server.ts
- Auth: email/password sign-up and sign-in, middleware.ts refreshes sessions
- Auth callback: app/auth/callback/route.ts
- Dashboard pages are server components that fetch data, then pass it to client components for interactivity
- Types defined in lib/types.ts (Habit, ContextLog)

## Current Status
- Issue 1 complete: repo initialized, Supabase schema migration created, RLS policies defined, env setup done
- Phase 1 in progress: auth, habits CRUD, today view with checklist still needed

## Phase 2 Requirements
- Context log entry form: when a user completes a habit, they can attach sleep_score (1-5), stress_score (1-5), mood (free text), schedule_disrupted (boolean), and notes
- History view: browse past context_logs by date at /dashboard/history
- Polish UI on core flows, handle edge cases (empty states, loading, errors)

## Phase 3 Requirements (later)
- AI insights page using Claude API via server actions
- Completion rate charts with Recharts over last 30 days
- Responsive layout, final deploy, README update

## Conventions
- Use server components by default, add "use client" only when needed for interactivity
- All Supabase queries on the server side go through lib/supabase/server.ts
- Client-side mutations use lib/supabase/client.ts and call router.refresh() after writes
- Keep components in the components/ directory
- No inline styles — use Tailwind utility classes
